# GitHub Deployment

This repo deploys from [vanshaj7-hub/test](https://github.com/vanshaj7-hub/test) via `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`.

## Workflow

- **CI** (every push/PR to `master` or `main`): `npm ci`, `npm run lint`, `npm run build`
- **Deploy** (push to `master`/`main` only): Vercel production deploy using prebuilt artifacts

## Required GitHub secrets

Set in **Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions**:

| Secret | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `VERCEL_TOKEN` | Vercel account token |
| `VERCEL_ORG_ID` | Team or user ID from Vercel project settings |
| `VERCEL_PROJECT_ID` | Project ID from Vercel project settings |

## Required GitHub variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` | Production site URL (used in CI build) |

## Vercel environment variables

Configure in the Vercel dashboard for production runtime:

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`
- `RESEND_API_KEY` (optional)
- `CONTACT_EMAIL` (optional)

## Conventions

- Do not commit `.env*` files; use GitHub Secrets and Vercel env vars instead.
- Keep deploy workflow on `master`/`main` branches only for production.
- Run `npm run build` locally before changing workflow or Next.js config.
